cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.SI, cs.DS, cs.NI. 

This paper deals with coding theory and information theory, specifically polar coding on binary erasure channels. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) is the most likely category. The paper also involves complexity analysis and algorithm design, which suggests cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as likely categories. The paper may also be relevant to cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) due to its focus on communication channels.
